<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px;">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
            <h2>Precision Irrigation FAQ</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Can I use precision irrigation in any shaped field?</summary><p>Yes. Our engineers design systems for irregular shapes, steep slopes, and any field size. Every layout is custom-designed for your land.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Does water quality affect the system?</summary><p>We account for water chemistry in system design. Filters, treatment options, and emitter selection are matched to your specific water source — including hard water, recycled water, and dairy effluent.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How will it change my fertilizer routine?</summary><p>Precision fertigation lets you deliver nutrients directly to roots in smaller, more frequent doses — typically reducing total fertilizer use by 20–40% while improving crop uptake.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What crops is it suitable for?</summary><p>All of them. We have purpose-built systems for row crops, orchards, vegetables, berries, tree nuts, grapes, hemp, and more. See our crop solutions page for specifics.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How long does installation take?</summary><p>Most farm installations are completed within a few days. Our crews work to minimize disruption to your ongoing operations.</p></details>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center mt-lg">
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Still Have Questions? Talk to an Expert</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
